stylometry: The concept of a saftey stock is the amount of left over inventory you have by the time the next order needs to be made or arrives. Saftey stock is inventory held in case the demand during lead time increases and you dont have enough on hand to meet that demand. Having saftey stock could save you in a time like this so you do not loose customers and or profit. But there is always a tradeoff having to much saftey stock could increase your holding costs so you want to balance the amount that you have so your holding costs dont get to expensinve exspecailly since its inventory that you plan on using just in case you run out during your lead time.
